description:
Watch as the story of Joseph from Genesis chapter 39 and Genesis chapter 40 comes to life in iBIBLE—the world’s first visual and interactive Bible. Featured in the 31st episode of iBIBLE is the story of Joseph as he works as a faithful servant in Egypt. Potiphar, who bought Joseph, is an officer of Pharaoh. Joseph is successful in all that he does and is set over his master’s house and all that he has. Potiphar’s wife notices Joseph, and asks him to come to bed with her, but he flees. Potiphar’s wife accuses Joseph, and he is put in prison. Study the Biblical Narrative and enjoy this presentation of God’s Word with iBIBLE.

A production of RevelationMedia, iBIBLE brings God’s Word to life in a format that people all over the world can engage with. Through dramatic audio and vibrant animation, people of all ages, all backgrounds, and with all abilities can learn the Biblical narrative—the one cohesive story of Scripture. iBIBLE will be available for free to translate into any of the world’s 7,000+ languages. Join the movement today and help bring the true story of God’s Word to the nations for free!

Visit www.iBIBLE.app to see all completed episodes of iBIBLE—a visual Bible for a visual and connected world! 

Director: Steve Cleary
